(secondQuint)Effectiveness of a Telephone Intervention to Improve the Mental Health of Abused Women.

 Depression is one of the most common mental health sequelae of intimate partner violence (IPV).

 Although a range of interventions have been tried to improve the mental health of women survivors of IPV, the results are inconclusive.

 In this trial, a 12-week advocacy intervention consisting of empowerment and telephone social support is provided to abused Chinese women in a community setting.

 Usual community services provide the control condition.

